commit_message:
[Docs] use openstack theme outside rtd

Rally team posts documentation at two places:
- http://rally.readthedocs.org/en/latest/ (preferable place)
- http://docs.openstack.org/developer/rally/

Most projects post docs at docs.o.o with oslosphinx theme. Since default
theme of sphinx is not so good, let's use official openstack theme instead.

Theme from oslosphinx has several issues:
- it is hard to find the link to home page of project documentation
- there is no sidebar with global content

Based on these two issues let's extend oslosphinx theme a bit.

Change-Id: Ifc75b430b7335c6a87a9102810ec33a5a913c43a

subject: updated cinder.conf for backup catalog info
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-04-18 15:57:13.000000000', 'files': ['defaults/main.yml', 'templates/cinder.conf.j2'], 'message': 'updated cinder.conf for backup catalog info

This change adds the variable ``cinder_swift_catalog_info`` to allow the
user to set the swift catalog URL information used when cinder backup
is used with swift. This option is required for the following reasons:

* When running SSL termination in front of all of the public APIs.
  If this option is unset the service will assume the "publicURL" is used.
  While this works in the AIO usecase in production its likely the
  publicURL is inaccessible from the service node.
* The volume service will not handle self-signed SSL certificats. If one
  is used the service will throw an SSLError and self signed certificates
  are likely to be common in private clouds with and without SSL
  termination.
* Performance will improve when using the internalURL vs the publicURL.

Change-Id: I63cfecd6793ba2b28c294d939c9b1c466940cbd1
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>
'}]
commit_message:
updated cinder.conf for backup catalog info

This change adds the variable ``cinder_swift_catalog_info`` to allow the
user to set the swift catalog URL information used when cinder backup
is used with swift. This option is required for the following reasons:

* When running SSL termination in front of all of the public APIs.
  If this option is unset the service will assume the "publicURL" is used.
  While this works in the AIO usecase in production its likely the
  publicURL is inaccessible from the service node.
* The volume service will not handle self-signed SSL certificats. If one
  is used the service will throw an SSLError and self signed certificates
  are likely to be common in private clouds with and without SSL
  termination.
* Performance will improve when using the internalURL vs the publicURL.

Change-Id: I63cfecd6793ba2b28c294d939c9b1c466940cbd1
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>

commit_message:
Don't look for invalid image keys for volume invalidation

When we want to test to see if we should invalidate the volume cache,
it's best to check the actual thing we care about, rather than some keys
that don't even exist.

Change-Id: Ic502729b3c44d8a14c97ad436ff3d5c5d73fa8f6

commit_message:
Fix server/hostname for RFC 1034/1035

This change ensures that the ``horizon_server_name`` option
is being set to the **ansible_hostname** fact if the facts are
available otherwise it will default to "horizon". This ensures
the Apache web server has an appropriate server name which is
compliant to the RFC.

Change-Id: Ibdeb8b981ca770ce4f56beeae05afd3379964859
Signed-off-by: Kevin Carter <kevin.carter@rackspace.com>

commit_message:
Fix scheduler_host_manager regression

Review [1] introduced a regression that reverted the updated value for
scheduler_host_manager made in review [2].  This old value worked fine
prior to newton but causes nova to fail to restart on newton.

This commit also removes the stale nova_scheduler_host_manager variable
which should no longer get used.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/293315/
[2] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/298450/

Change-Id: Iedf3892d6317cb3566e40460bdbb05d15b4641ae

subject: Dynamically determine whether Neutron Agents should be enabled
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-04-20 09:02:58.000000000', 'files': ['releasenotes/notes/neutron-agent-dynamic-enable-47f0c709ef0dfe55.yaml', 'defaults/main.yml'], 'message': "Dynamically determine whether Neutron Agents should be enabled

Both the Nuage and PLUMgrid configuration guides advocate overwriting
the entire neutron_services dict in order to disable the DHCP,
Metadata and LinuxBridge Agents. This method is prone to error and
should ideally be more dynamic.

This patch implements a more dynamic approach based on the
neutron_plugin_type and the neutron_ml2_mechanism_drivers that are
set.

This will hopefully simplify the configuration of these and other
ML2 mechanisms (eg: openvswitch) when they're implemented.

Change-Id: I38e1fad4dfae24b32f4370b3da16561c42cd670d
"}]
commit_message:
Dynamically determine whether Neutron Agents should be enabled

Both the Nuage and PLUMgrid configuration guides advocate overwriting
the entire neutron_services dict in order to disable the DHCP,
Metadata and LinuxBridge Agents. This method is prone to error and
should ideally be more dynamic.

This patch implements a more dynamic approach based on the
neutron_plugin_type and the neutron_ml2_mechanism_drivers that are
set.

This will hopefully simplify the configuration of these and other
ML2 mechanisms (eg: openvswitch) when they're implemented.

Change-Id: I38e1fad4dfae24b32f4370b3da16561c42cd670d

commit_message:
Correct Neutron VPNaaS service_provider config entry

When we run os-neutron.yml the playbook runs without a
problem but neutron stops working because the service
provider are using the wrong python module (neutron)
instead of the the (neutron_vpnaas) which has the

commit_message:
Update swift proxy logic for healthcheck service

With network template updates, we need to properly configure the service
healthcheck to match the expected HAproxy configuration. This change
ensure the healthcheck service is properly configured when it needs to
be.

Change-Id: I1647c2a6142ea2f7fbe7eb8a5eda0deb962cdd6c
Closes-Bug: #1548275

commit_message:
Lower our nodepool-base finalise.d script

This is needed because we need 11-selinux-fixfiles-restore from
rpm-distro to run after us, so we can properly restore SELinux
security contexts.

We can also remove restorecon functionality, since it doesn't work in
chroots on ubuntu build servers.

Change-Id: Ic9ffb121d5950d9028061591a346a5228fe89214
Signed-off-by: Paul Belanger <pabelanger@redhat.com>

Without insist, lsyncd will quit if any of its slaves are unavailable at
startup. This enforces a strict restart ordering - the master repo

commit_message:
Add insist option to lsyncd

Without insist, lsyncd will quit if any of its slaves are unavailable at
startup. This enforces a strict restart ordering - the master repo
server must come up last.

In order to remove this restriction the -insist option is added to
lsyncd. This causes lsyncd to retry the initial connection to each slave
so that even if the master comes up first, connections will eventually
be established.

Change-Id: I12e3dca147b5cb25ed982d5aceb9d521728c4e53
Closes-Bug: #1572433
(cherry picked from commit bbc038c87bf80a7fbff76ba4fbf813f08d5ef574)

and AODH_SERVICE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8042 if they are not set.

commit_message:
Add wait_for_openwswitch_agent function

Sometimes neutron opnwsitch agent can't start in time.
As result port can't be bound because of missing agent.
This patch adds wait_for_openwswitch_agent function that
allows to wait for openvswitch agent to start before
executing actual test.

Change-Id: Id99157a1db4f134b45eb68bbfeb1708ba5df9ddc
Closes-Bug: #1572531

commit_message:
Colorize logging output

This patch colorize all logging.StreamHandler output. The best way to try
it launch dummy scenarios in debug mode.

Also, it adds print_in_red, print_in_yellow, print_in_green and print_in_cyan
methods, which are supposed to be used in CLI. Output of

commit_message:
tripleo.sh --delorean-build handle oslo.* package builds

Currently oslo package builds fail because of an inconsistency where
the rdoinfo data expects e.g "oslo-utils", but the repo name is "oslo.utils".

This adjusts the names, so you can do e.g

tripleo.sh --delorean-build openstack/oslo.utils

Change-Id: I220756751d4844def1d9f260b1fa64c384c2cfc4

commit_message:
restore tagging ACLs for independent projects

This change partially reverts "update tag ACLs for all official
projects" (commit a4c8a7f0a24b51c0c90dad78694e6ed74dfb5b64) to restore
tagging ACLs to projects not following a cycle-based release model.

Change-Id: I1110be7f73f8db836934a2c630642d73cd340a36
Signed-off-by: Doug Hellmann <doug@doughellmann.com>

commit_message:
ODL Overcloud Image

Add new option for building odl (opendaylight) overcloud image.

To build the new odl image you can use "--odl"  in addition to "--all" or
"--type=overcloud-odl".

To upload the odl image you can use "openstack overcloud image upload --odl"

Change-Id: I218858fe31d3726b8a85f698a8d8a9e744dc0604

commit_message:
Validate attributes restrictions

Since Nailgun contains attributes restriction
mechanism it's possible to verify attributes
restrictions. This commit applies restrictions
checks into validation for both node attributes
and cluster attributes.

Change-Id: I269da9a7a7df5fea336c07784b37d6ced1641993
Closes-Bug: #1567394
(cherry picked from commit 7e3fe2c308918f4f8abc42ad7d1584b4e4afadfc)

commit_message:

commit_message:
Run the tests inside the test directory

This change allows the test runner to be executed everywhere without
having a .testr.conf file. A copy of .testr.conf file (which is now
properly released and installed) is copied to the test directory, which
is now used as working directory for the ostestr call.
The path to the directory where the execution has been started is now
passed to the test template, so that the code can write there data like
the test reports, the key (if the resources are kept), etc.

Change-Id: I16ddba2ad6e26381ffc4b447666f38f2a7740ecb

commit_message:
Rebase: proper '_' import, deprecated xags

1) We were not importing '_' in exceptions.py, so we were using the
default symbol from builtins, which isn't the right thing for
translation.  Import from this project's i18n module instead (and use
_LE, for they are exceptions).  It would also seem as though it is now a
requirement to import _ from a module at <project>._i18n; so the
networking_powervm.plugins.ibm.agent.powervm.i18n module has been moved
there.

2) The VIOS.xags property is deprecated.  Rebase to use
pypowervm.const.XAG instead.

Change-Id: Ief47001b5525dda88c9c72c16b92505c3f974950

commit_message:
Check Keystone init before running it

It turns out that os-cloud-config is smart enough to not re-create
Keystone resources if they already exist, which means the previous
check for whether Puppet had already initialized it didn't work.

As an alternative, explicitly check whether the nova user has been
created before running init.  If it does already exist, then don't
even run the Keystone init.

Some refactoring was also done to enable easier unit testing of the
change.

Change-Id: Ifa741aaa9f2c60e82272e3d855c57f36834d2220
(cherry picked from commit dc39d73446a9fd24e913f9e2dbd844b00d3659a8)

Fuelmenu doesn't need to report ERROR level log when reporting
"Unable to read YAML: /etc/fuel/astute.yaml" because we have no
default astute.yaml any more.

commit_message:
Use Ironic API v1.11 to support ENROLL state

This state was introduced in Liberty as a new state for freshly enrolled
nodes, but is only exposed to clients who specify an API version >=
1.11. We add a new --initial-state parameter to `openstack baremetal
import` to enable use of the new state.

Change-Id: If04889c3778827a77236f6d88617211ecc0f4161

could pass has no sense (ICMP will be fragmented).

commit_message:
Make task version check in lcm serializer optional

The option LCM_CHECK_TASK_VERSION will control
task serializer allows to start deploy with tasks
that have version less than 2.0.0 or not.

commit_message:
Enhance testing approach

Make following changes:
- Use 'ostestr' lib for running tests instead of
  own obsolete implementation (run_tests.sh script).
- Make 'cover' job work adding 'tools/cover.sh' script.
- Fix settings file for tests for proper work with 'ostestr'.

To run "coverage" tox job do following:

$ tox -e cover

Note, that it will provide correct results when one more new commits
appears. Because 'cover' job uses not one, but two latest commits.

Change-Id: Ie1c640a575951159503db091b3191c709959c96a

commit_message:
Add middleware to track template rendering time

Adds a simple middleware to track and log how
much time does it take to render a template.
Also adds the time to the cookies as
X-TIME-RENDER-TEMPLATE for easy access to times.
Only active if TEMPLATE_DEBUG=True

Change-Id: I05dab44542637cd09c6ad672c21f69deb4a2c8ef
Closes-Bug: #1533748

commit_message:
Fix resource discovery for datasources

The lookahead code which checks path to source files and ssl certificate
did not properly consider the shared resources when package is installed.
Now data source files are looked locally first and then, if not found and
the path is relative, inside the default templates directory.
The default paths for test resources have been then changed to use defaults/
as base directory, with the exception of unit tests.
As the file referenced by yaml files must now exist, a new dummy file .crt
file was added for unit tests.

Change-Id: Ic385c6b4d694d95a11a626a3107fa1906924bd67

commit_message:
Add insist option to lsyncd

Without insist, lsyncd will quit if any of its slaves are unavailable at
startup. This enforces a strict restart ordering - the master repo
server must come up last.

In order to remove this restriction the -insist option is added to
lsyncd. This causes lsyncd to retry the initial connection to each slave
so that even if the master comes up first, connections will eventually
be established.

Change-Id: I12e3dca147b5cb25ed982d5aceb9d521728c4e53
Closes-Bug: #1572433

commit_message:
User facing error Summary Messages

The purpose of this spec is to define a mechanism in Cinder that will
allow a user to see error messages for asynchronous operations.

This is more specific to failed operations and cause of their failure.

Spec started in Newton

APIImpact New /messages resource

DocImpact

Co-Authored-By: Alex Meade <mr.alex.meade@gmail.com>

Implements : blueprint summarymessage

Change-Id: If7f8b7f277863a6dbf9686dadab145590ec9567d

subject: Fix event listeners
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2016-04-20 07:50:59.000000000', 'files': ['os_win/__init__.py', 'os_win/utils/compute/clusterutils.py', 'os_win/utils/compute/vmutils.py', 'os_win/utils/network/networkutils.py', 'os_win/tests/utils/compute/test_clusterutils.py', 'os_win/tests/utils/compute/test_vmutils.py', 'os_win/tests/utils/network/test_networkutils.py'], 'message': 'Fix event listeners

PyMI subscribes to event providers, setting a callback that will be
invoked when an event arrives. When called, the event watcher will
block until an event is retrieved. A threading.Event is used
internally by PyMI for the event waiting workflow.

The issue is that the threading module will be monkey patched by
eventlet. The event callback is performed from a different thread, so
attempting to set the event for which the event watcher waits will
some times raise the "error: cannot switch to a different thread"
greenlet exception, thus breaking the event listener.

This issue can be fixed at the os-win level, without PyMI having to
know about eventlet monkey patching. We can make sure that PyMI uses
the unpatched threading module, also ensuring that the blocking calls
are run in a different thread, so that we don't block the calling
thread. eventlet.tpool can be used to easily achieve this.

Closes-Bug: #1568824

Change-Id: I9be6c1a1b144bdf565f25517c52439a5fb10cb51

Events: use tpool only if thread module is patched

At the moment, we use eventlet.tpool when waiting for events
even if the 'thread' module is not monkey patched, which causes
locking issues.

This patch changes this, checking if the 'thread' module is monkey
patched, otherwise calling the method waiting for events directly.

Related-Bug: #1568824

Change-Id: Ib752bfa2acc9f6b47996f6e949aadf20903c849b
(cherry-picked from commit 356b6cca37fd90c9ae449cf4bb0d2cddf480a34b)

commit_message:
Fix event listeners

PyMI subscribes to event providers, setting a callback that will be
invoked when an event arrives. When called, the event watcher will
block until an event is retrieved. A threading.Event is used
internally by PyMI for the event waiting workflow.

The issue is that the threading module will be monkey patched by
eventlet. The event callback is performed from a different thread, so
attempting to set the event for which the event watcher waits will
some times raise the "error: cannot switch to a different thread"
greenlet exception, thus breaking the event listener.

This issue can be fixed at the os-win level, without PyMI having to
know about eventlet monkey patching. We can make sure that PyMI uses
the unpatched threading module, also ensuring that the blocking calls
are run in a different thread, so that we don't block the calling
thread. eventlet.tpool can be used to easily achieve this.

Closes-Bug: #1568824

Change-Id: I9be6c1a1b144bdf565f25517c52439a5fb10cb51
(cherry picked from commit 53a8d6d0b3381e6df2823257fa1aa1665077cea4)

Events: use tpool only if thread module is patched

At the moment, we use eventlet.tpool when waiting for events
even if the 'thread' module is not monkey patched, which causes
locking issues.

This patch changes this, checking if the 'thread' module is monkey
patched, otherwise calling the method waiting for events directly.

Related-Bug: #1568824

Change-Id: Ib752bfa2acc9f6b47996f6e949aadf20903c849b
(cherry-picked from commit 356b6cca37fd90c9ae449cf4bb0d2cddf480a34b)

commit_message:
Remove explicit 'cluster' argument from UpdateOpenstackConfigTask

"cluster" argument for method UpdateOpenstackConfigTask.message
is redudnant, since it can be retrieved from "task.cluster".
It also causes TypeError when trying to call method
message when LCM is supported, because ClusterTransaction.message
does not have "cluster" attribute.

Change-Id: I1de41b819ade7d8c7ff467e5664b6f4c9bb295a3
Closes-Bug: #1571542
(cherry picked from commit ecda041e484a2d46a0e409435062c196d1a60483)

commit_message:
Don't disconnect br-int from phys br if connected

When starting up, we don't want to delete the patch port between br-int
and the physical bridges. In liberty the br-int bridge was changed to
not tear down flows on startup, and  change
I9801b76829021c9a0e6358982e1136637634a521 will change the physical
bridges to not tear down flows also.

Without this patch the patch port is torn down and not reinstalled until
after the initial flows are set back up.

Partial-Bug: #1514056
Change-Id: I05bf5105a6f3acf6a313ce6799648a095cf8ec96
(cherry picked from commit a549f30fad93508bf9dfdcfb20cd522f7add27b0)

commit_message:
Cleanup stale OVS flows for physical bridges

Perform deletion of the stale flows in physical bridges consistently with
br-int and br-tun, respecting drop_flows_on_start configuration option.
Added tests for auxiliary bridge and functional tests for the physical
bridge using VLAN/flat external network. Fixes part of the bug 1514056;
together with [1] and [2], the bug should be considered fixed.

The commit also fixes inconsistency between netmask of allocated IP
addresses assigned in _create_test_port_dict and ip_len in _plug_ports
of base.py.

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/297211/
[2] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/297818/

Co-Authored-By: Jian Wen <wenjianhn@gmail.com>
Partial-Bug: 1514056
Change-Id: I9801b76829021c9a0e6358982e1136637634a521
(cherry picked from commit cacde308eef6f1d7005e555b4521332da95d3cf4)

commit_message:
Allow add/delete networks ports as a tenant

Creates add/remove ports on the project network dashboard.
Reuses the same actions/forms/templates/views for the
admin to not duplicate code.
Changes tests to check that admin views are using the
project templates.
Adds a utility method to get the breadcrumb for the port
detail page so it can be overriden from the admin dash.

Change-Id: I30d4180902109bfe6b4a3bf002f426379e90643d
Implements: blueprint network-ports-tenant

commit_message:
Get MACs from /interfaces instead of node meta

Use nodes interfaces data (can't be changed after deployment)
instead of nodes metadata (can be updated after deployment) while
comparing nodes MACs, because when user enables DPDK for some
interface, it disappears from node meta after deployment.

Change-Id: Ibecc244194de3b449ba0a6181d0979bbd7ca0b39
Closes-bug: #1565706

commit_message:
Enable Mesos Bay export more slave flags

The Mesos slave has many different flags and different user have
different requirement for different parameters, add isolation,
work_dir, image_providers parameters for slave in mesos bay to
give end user more choice. for example Set the parameters to
support Container Images in Mesos Containerizer

Note: support Container Images in Mesos Containerizer needs mesos
version >= 0.28
Partially-Implements:blueprint mesos-slave-flags

Change-Id: Ib4fd7076704a3266f0cf2addf08896729ec6062f

subject: Fix event listeners
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-04-19 12:32:10.000000000', 'files': ['os_win/__init__.py', 'os_win/utils/compute/clusterutils.py', 'os_win/utils/compute/vmutils.py', 'os_win/utils/network/networkutils.py', 'os_win/tests/utils/compute/test_clusterutils.py', 'os_win/tests/utils/compute/test_vmutils.py', 'os_win/tests/utils/network/test_networkutils.py'], 'message': 'Fix event listeners

PyMI subscribes to event providers, setting a callback that will be
invoked when an event arrives. When called, the event watcher will
block until an event is retrieved. A threading.Event is used
internally by PyMI for the event waiting workflow.

The issue is that the threading module will be monkey patched by
eventlet. The event callback is performed from a different thread, so
attempting to set the event for which the event watcher waits will
some times raise the "error: cannot switch to a different thread"
greenlet exception, thus breaking the event listener.

This issue can be fixed at the os-win level, without PyMI having to
know about eventlet monkey patching. We can make sure that PyMI uses
the unpatched threading module, also ensuring that the blocking calls
are run in a different thread, so that we don't block the calling
thread. eventlet.tpool can be used to easily achieve this.

Closes-Bug: #1568824

Change-Id: I9be6c1a1b144bdf565f25517c52439a5fb10cb51
(cherry picked from commit 53a8d6d0b3381e6df2823257fa1aa1665077cea4)
'}]
commit_message:
Fix event listeners

PyMI subscribes to event providers, setting a callback that will be
invoked when an event arrives. When called, the event watcher will
block until an event is retrieved. A threading.Event is used
internally by PyMI for the event waiting workflow.

The issue is that the threading module will be monkey patched by
eventlet. The event callback is performed from a different thread, so
attempting to set the event for which the event watcher waits will
some times raise the "error: cannot switch to a different thread"
greenlet exception, thus breaking the event listener.

This issue can be fixed at the os-win level, without PyMI having to
know about eventlet monkey patching. We can make sure that PyMI uses
the unpatched threading module, also ensuring that the blocking calls
are run in a different thread, so that we don't block the calling
thread. eventlet.tpool can be used to easily achieve this.

Closes-Bug: #1568824

Change-Id: I9be6c1a1b144bdf565f25517c52439a5fb10cb51
(cherry picked from commit 53a8d6d0b3381e6df2823257fa1aa1665077cea4)

commit_message:
Update dependency for betamax to 0.6.0

Latest betamax release is needed for keystoneauth and
shade projects.
This new version adds a functionality that enables to record
different interactions for same url and parameters. This will
allow to improve the workflow of our tests in keystoneauth and
shade.

Change-Id: I567e77fc79cc11836b65acab1bbf81daabd409f1

commit_message:
Template loaders defined before local settings

TEMPLATE_LOADERS was defined after loading local_settings.py and was sqashing
any attempt to customize the template loaders.
This patch adds CACHED_TEMPLATE_LOADERS, ADD_TEMPLATE_LOADERS and a doc
defining how to use them in order to ease customization process.

Change-Id: I2544529ee965ef01c6ac4973056801ebee50be6d
Closes-Bug: #1568764

commit_message:
Remove extra loops from upload_cirros script

This change removes the extra loops from the upload_cirros script that
were added while attempting to debug Bug 1556068.  These extra loops
could cause the task to exceed the task timeout and ultimately did not
address the main issue. This change cleans up the extra code that was
added for debugging purposes now that the previous bug has been closed.

Change-Id: I26cfe1d0f6f2f6d8fb2e9fbba2cd964574c7bbef
Closes-Bug: #1563981
(cherry picked from commit 031df97cb9cccb80cda562a2782aaf2c7fe45cba)

commit_message:
Smooth out glance api servers getter

* get glance api servers list from one entry point for http(s)
* set the following descending priority for getter:
  - hiera glance_api_servers raw list
  - get_ssl_property() return
  - hiera glance_endpoint ip address
  - $management_vip

Change-Id: I80c45d1c6cdabfd8aa239ae61d8c4add5e9e8cbe
Closes-Bug: #1568088
Closes-bug: #1569443
(cherry picked from commit 2e1ed9749d65ab9ec099f3e01a445569a075613c)

[{'number': 2, 'created': '2016-04-19 07:58:05.000000000', 'files': ['tox.ini'], 'message': 'Fix tox -e py34

tox.ini:

* add py34 to the envlist. We must add it before py27 to workaround a
  bug with the testrepository database. If we run tox -e py27 first,
  it creates the database in a format not readable by Python 3. If we
  run tox -e py34 first, Python 2 and Python 3 are happy with the

commit_message:
Fix tox -e py34

tox.ini:

* add py34 to the envlist. We must add it before py27 to workaround a
  bug with the testrepository database. If we run tox -e py27 first,
  it creates the database in a format not readable by Python 3. If we
  run tox -e py34 first, Python 2 and Python 3 are happy with the
  database.
* py34: add a whitelist of tests known to pass on Python 3.

Blueprint: murano-python-3-support
Change-Id: I96ae09faec0bbb58e111838ab95109a6acd9c53d

commit_message:
Use enable-packages-install

Use the enable-packages-install element instead of
undercloud-package-install.  The elements are equivalent in what they
do, and switching over will enable us to get rid of
undercloud-package-install.

commit_message:
Added js-afs-blob-store to openstack-infra

This project is an implementation of the fs-blob-store, which exposes
an API that appears to be a real POSIX filesystem, but in reality
is a file renaming shim which sorts all documents into alphabetical
directories. /foo becomes /f/foo, /bar becomes /b/bar, etc.

Change-Id: Icbaa3d28650583599d20f273ef65757783a73674
Depends-on: Ic969dd933349f718409dc9357b25ff13c0e02d29

subject: fix heartbeat is blocked by listener.wait()
revisions:
[{'number': 3, 'created': '2016-04-14 02:19:56.000000000', 'files': ['ceilometer/notification.py'], 'message': "fix heartbeat is blocked by listener.wait()

When a new process/member join the group, tooz will re-distribute
the tasks to all members, then the old members may need to kill
some listeners because its task is reduced.

However, oslo_messaging kills a listener by calling a blocking
method wait(), which becomes worse if there are many listeners,
and listener holds some resources to clear, some listeners might
take dozens of seconds to exit.

The heartbeat has no chance to execute during the process of killing
the listeners, hence it will leave the group automatically,
after all listeners exit, it will find itself doesn't in the group,
so it will rejoin the group, which back into the first stage .....

This patch fixes it by adding heartbeat after listener is killed,
to make sure it remains in the group.

Change-Id: I61dcf37d590ea1e190455bfb681467d359dd060a
Closes-Bug: #1566887
"}]
commit_message:
fix heartbeat is blocked by listener.wait()

When a new process/member join the group, tooz will re-distribute
the tasks to all members, then the old members may need to kill
some listeners because its task is reduced.

However, oslo_messaging kills a listener by calling a blocking
method wait(), which becomes worse if there are many listeners,
and listener holds some resources to clear, some listeners might
take dozens of seconds to exit.

The heartbeat has no chance to execute during the process of killing
the listeners, hence it will leave the group automatically,
after all listeners exit, it will find itself doesn't in the group,
so it will rejoin the group, which back into the first stage .....

This patch fixes it by adding heartbeat after listener is killed,
to make sure it remains in the group.

Change-Id: I61dcf37d590ea1e190455bfb681467d359dd060a
Closes-Bug: #1566887

commit_message:
update remove_export() with versionedobjects

The following patch updates remove_export()
API to use volume versionedobjects.  Changes were
made to be backwards compatible with older RPC clients.
It only includes changes to the core cinder code.
Changes in the drivers are left to each driver
maintainer to update.

Co-Authored-By: Thang Pham <thang.g.pham@gmail.com>

Partial-Implements: blueprint cinder-objects
Change-Id: I78195241a49bab4fcba9a1167877d9031b991dcb

commit_message:
Update copy_volume_to_image to use volume object

The copy_volume_to_image API is now able to use volume versioned
objects.

Note that this patch DOES NOT try to use object dot notation everywhere
to keep the size small. This cleanup will be done in the future.

Change-Id: Iead86f372b1ec936ad0b6f2b2bacb460c733c687
Partial-Implements: blueprint cinder-objects

where MAAS zones are not configured (i.e. nothing other than the

commit_message:
Revert "add juju availability zone to ceph osd location when present"

This reverts commit c94e0b4b0e6c0cbda1c2c09b4189fe2ad9bf447f.

Support for juju provided zones was broken on older Ceph releases
where MAAS zones are not configured (i.e. nothing other than the
default zone).

Backing this change out until we can provide a more complete and
backwards compatible solution.

Closes-Bug: 1570960

Change-Id: I889d556d180d47b54af2991a65efcca09d685332

commit_message:
Update terminate_connection() with versionedobjects

The following patch updates terminate_connection
API to use volume versionedobjects.  Changes were
made to be backwards compatible with older RPC clients.
It only includes changes to the core cinder code.
Changes in the drivers are left to each driver
maintainer to update.

Co-Authored-By: Thang Pham <thang.g.pham@gmail.com>

Partial-Implements: blueprint cinder-objects
Change-Id: I2f19ef45e86d0df80d8733a0e2a5cfdd372c2fb7

commit_message:
Update restore_backup to use volume object

The restore_backup API is now able to use volume versioned objects.

Note that this patch DOES NOT try to use object dot notation everywhere
to keep the size small. This cleanup will be done in the future.

Change-Id: I7c2322547cdead270b9cd7868c064cdf72dfa7b9
Partial-Implements: blueprint cinder-objects

commit_message:
Update create_snapshot to use volume object

The create_snapshot flow is now using volume versioned objects.

Note that this patch DOES NOT try to use object dot notation everywhere
to keep the size small. This cleanup will be done in the future.

Change-Id: Ic07f82c1e894cbd7e0d441e5bfb40b8cd4c340ce
Partial-Implements: blueprint cinder-objects

commit_message:
Update replication to use versionedobjects

The following patch updates following methods
to use volume versionedobjects:
* enable_replication
* disable_replication
* reenable_replication
* failover_replication
* list_replication_targets
* promote_replica
It only includes changes to the core cinder code.
Changes in the drivers are left to each driver
maintainer to update.

Co-Authored-By: Thang Pham <thang.g.pham@gmail.com>
Partial-Implements: blueprint cinder-objects
Change-Id: I55c4d843b10dbd9424cd9f8892f6430e04045b31

commit_message:
Switch main bootstrap source repository to online one

In case of deploying Fuel Master node on a pre-provisioned
server, we should use online repositories instead of local
ones, to build the Ubuntu bootstrap.

commit_message:
Add option to auto enable from VPNaaS in Horizon

This change simple provides an option to inspect the neutron_plugin_base
and enable vpnaas within horizon if the option is found.
